# {{ program_name }} — Knowledge Database (KDB)

## Overview

The **Knowledge Database (KDB)** is the **Single Source of Truth (SSOT)** for all engineering data in the {{ program_name }} program.

## Structure

```
KDB/
├── requirements/       # Engineering requirements
│   ├── system/         # System requirements
│   ├── safety/         # Safety requirements
│   └── certification/  # Certification requirements
│
├── design/             # Design data
│   ├── models/         # 3D models (STEP, CATIA)
│   ├── drawings/       # Engineering drawings
│   └── analysis/       # Analysis reports
│
├── parts/              # Parts and BOM data
│   ├── bom/            # Bills of material
│   └── catalog/        # Parts catalog data
│
├── tasks/              # Maintenance task data
│   ├── scheduled/      # Scheduled maintenance
│   └── unscheduled/    # Unscheduled maintenance
│
├── repairs/            # Structural repair data
│   ├── standard/       # Standard repairs
│   └── allowable/      # Allowable damage limits
│
└── faults/             # Fault and troubleshooting data
    ├── isolation/      # Fault isolation procedures
    └── symptoms/       # Symptom-fault correlation
```

## Governance

- **Authority:** Engineering owns KDB content
- **Baseline:** KDB content is baselined per ASIT governance
- **Changes:** All changes require ECR/ECO process
- **Traceability:** All content linked to requirements

## Usage

KDB content is transformed to IDB (CSDB) through ASIGT under ASIT contract control.

```
KDB (Engineering Truth) → ASIGT → IDB (Operational Information)
```

## Important

> **KDB is the authoritative source.**  
> Do not modify IDB content directly — regenerate from KDB.

